&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Renal Nurse Specialist&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Renal Vaccination &amp; Transplant&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a rare opportunity to join the small but rapidly growing &amp; dynamic team of Transplant Specialist Nurses.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The role includes the oversight and governance of the hospital and community based hepatitis B vaccine programme for all prospective dialysis patients ensuring immunization throughout their pre dialysis journey.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The second and separate part of the role involves working with and supporting renal transplant recipients, within the outpatient setting, throughout their transplant journey. You will be involved in preparing &amp; assessing the renal patients for both live donor &amp; cadaver transplant suitability.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In both of these roles you will be supported to develop skills to see patients autonomously within the virtual and face to face clinic setting. We will welcome applications from capable and enthusiastic individuals, who have experience working in the renal/transplant setting, or have transferable skills, and want to be part of our busy, dynamic, forwarding thinking team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will need to have good communication, organisational &amp; prioritising skills, the ability to learn and develop quickly; work autonomously and as part of a multi-disciplinary team in a busy environment. There is the opportunity to undertake further educational development to enhance your skills.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Transplant Nurse Specialist, Gemma Fox on 07919571077 or 01305 254546&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Matron, Kathleen O’Neill on 01305 253745 or 07825 40004&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
